<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 01 at 6:59PM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A LINE OF SHOWERS WILL AFFECT
NORTHWESTERN ALLEGHANY AND WEST CENTRAL BATH COUNTIES IN WEST CENTRAL
VIRGINIA...CENTRAL TAZEWELL COUNTY IN SOUTHWESTERN VIRGINIA...
SOUTHERN GREENBRIER...SUMMERS...MERCER AND NORTHWESTERN MONROE
COUNTIES IN SOUTHEASTERN WEST VIRGINIA...
At 658 PM EST, radar indicated showers were located along a line
extending from near Williamsburg to Grundy. Movement was east at 55
mph.
Winds in excess of 30 mph are possible with these showers.
Locations impacted include...
Bluefield...
Princeton...
Tazewell...
Lewisburg...
Hinton...
White Sulphur Springs...
and Ronceverte.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</description>
